## Needs & priorities (inputs)

| Area | Includes |
|------|----------|
| **Preventive health** | Promotion, immunisation, screening, early detection |
| **Education & awareness** | Health literacy, school health, dialogues, behaviour change |
| **Vulnerable groups** | Women & mothers, children & adolescents, elderly, disabilities, refugees, urban poor |

## Services & enablers (outputs)

| Area | Includes |
|------|----------|
| **Livelihoods & enterprise** | CHIS, IGAs, savings groups, entrepreneurship, skills |
| **Data & feedback** | Community data, monitoring, learning, continuous improvement |
| **Partnerships & resources** | Government, NGOs & CBOs, academia, donors, private sector |

## How to use

- Frame FairBanks as a **community health ecosystem**, not only a clinic.
- FCHIP is a **FairBanks component** — the intelligence layer on this cascade (CHW/VHT, schools, communities, hospitals, clinics; GIS/climate; Data & Feedback).
- Keep vulnerable groups, livelihoods/CHIS, and partners visible where relevant.
- Prefer human language; keep cascade order; use concept visuals in decks (see `documents.mdc`).
